Business Brief -- Hershey Foods Corp.:
   Chocolate Concern's Profits
   Rose 61% for 4th Quarter
The company said that in the latest quarter, Hershey
Chocolate U.S.A. was the major contributor to earnings
growth, helped by price increases and lower marketing
expenses related to product introductions.
   For all of 1991, net income rose 1.7% to $219.5 million,
or $2.43 a share, from $215.9 million, or $2.39 a share. The
year-earlier figure included a $20.3 million after-tax gain.
Sales grew 6.8% to $2.9 billion from $2.72 billion.